    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "AI image tools make pretty pictures.\n\nThe hard part is getting them on-brand and consistent, post after post.\n\nHere are the 7 steps to make AI produce visuals and infographics that look like one brand:",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2065694408625074380",
    "time": "2026-06-13 15:15",
    "created_at": "Sat Jun 13 07:15:00 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2065694408625074380",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "1. Lock the Brand Kit\n\nBefore generating anything, write down the rules every visual follows. Colors, fonts, spacing, the look you're after.\n\nExample: a short brand sheet with your exact hex codes and two font names, pasted into every image prompt so the model stops guessing.",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2065694420620755108",
    "time": "2026-06-13 15:15",
    "created_at": "Sat Jun 13 07:15:03 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2065694420620755108",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "2. Brief the Visual\n\nTurn the content into a one-line brief: what it's for, the single idea it shows, and where it'll be posted.\n\nExample: \"Feed image, 4:5, one stat with a short caption, dark background.\" A clear brief beats a vague \"make it look good.\"",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2065694432176095337",
    "time": "2026-06-13 15:15",
    "created_at": "Sat Jun 13 07:15:06 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2065694432176095337",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "3. Draft the Layout First\n\nGet the structure right before you touch style. Decide what goes where and what the eye reads first.\n\nExample: ask the model for three rough layout options as plain boxes, pick one, then style only the winner.",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2065694443693600992",
    "time": "2026-06-13 15:15",
    "created_at": "Sat Jun 13 07:15:08 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2065694443693600992",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "4. Generate On-Brand\n\nFeed the brief and the brand kit into your image model and generate. Same rules in, consistent look out.\n\nExample: GPT Image for a clean infographic or hero image, with your palette and layout baked into the prompt.",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2065694455236341868",
    "time": "2026-06-13 15:15",
    "created_at": "Sat Jun 13 07:15:11 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2065694455236341868",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "5. Fix the Text\n\nImage models still mangle text. Do a dedicated pass to correct the words, spacing, and alignment.\n\nExample: a text-edit model like Nano Banana Pro to swap the garbled headline for the exact words you wrote.",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2065694466762219899",
    "time": "2026-06-13 15:15",
    "created_at": "Sat Jun 13 07:15:14 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2065694466762219899",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "6. Run the Brand Check\n\nBefore it ships, hold the visual against your brand kit. Right colors, right fonts, right feel, readable on a phone.\n\nExample: a 5-point checklist you run every time, so nothing off-brand slips out because it looked fine at a glance.",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2065694478334369972",
    "time": "2026-06-13 15:15",
    "created_at": "Sat Jun 13 07:15:17 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2065694478334369972",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "7. Save the Recipe\n\nWhen one comes out right, save the prompt, the settings, and the layout as a template you can reuse.\n\nExample: a \"stat card\" recipe you reload next week and only change the numbers, so post 50 looks like post 1.",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2065694489910677849",
    "time": "2026-06-13 15:15",
    "created_at": "Sat Jun 13 07:15:19 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2065694489910677849",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "String these together and your visuals look like one brand instead of random AI output.\n\nThe tools render the pixels, but you set the standard they have to hit.",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2065694501524631800",
    "time": "2026-06-13 15:15",
    "created_at": "Sat Jun 13 07:15:22 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2065694501524631800",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
